Business Brief -- LDDS Communications Inc.:
   SEC Clears Unit's Merger
   With Salt Lake City Firm
Separately, LDDS, based in Jackson, Miss., said it
acquired Shared Use Network Systems Inc. of Phoenix, Ariz.,
and the New Mexico operations of Automated Communications
Inc., based in Denver, for about $5 million in cash and
stock. Those operations have combined annual revenues of $8
million, LDDS said.